  "prompt": "Why is Quora flooded with questions on iit and iim only?",
  "response": "Quora tends to have a high volume of questions about IITs (Indian Institutes of Technology) and IIMs (Indian Institutes of Management) for several reasons:\n\n1. **Prestige and Reputation**: IITs and IIMs are among the most prestigious educational institutions in India. They are known for their rigorous academic standards and the high caliber of graduates, which draws significant interest.\n\n2. **Career Opportunities**: Graduates from IITs and IIMs often have better career prospects, leading to discussions about admissions, preparation strategies, and the benefits of attending these institutions.\n\n3. **Competitive Exams**: The entrance exams for IITs (JEE Advanced) and IIMs (CAT) are highly competitive and generate a lot of queries from students seeking advice on preparation, study materials, and strategies.\n\n4. **Placement Success**: These institutions are known for their strong placement records, which piques interest from not just aspiring students but also parents and educators.\n\n5. **Cultural Phenomenon**: The focus on IITs and IIMs has become somewhat of a cultural phenomenon in India, with many students viewing admission to these schools as a significant achievement.\n\n6. **Community and Information Sharing**: Quora serves as a platform for individuals to ask questions and share experiences. The high volume of questions creates a feedback loop, where more questions inspire others to ask similar ones.\n\n7. **Information Asymmetry**: Many students and parents may feel overwhelmed by the admission process and seek guidance, leading to a proliferation of questions in this area.\n\nDue to these factors, discussions on IITs and IIMs become a prominent topic on platforms like Quora, reflecting the interests and concerns of many individuals in the Indian education system.",
